channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Cornell University Antisemite Sentenced to Prison for Threatening to Slaughter Jewish Students
Late Rep. Sheila Jackson Lee's daughter running for mother's old House seat: 'I want to finish for my mom!'
item.description: Late Rep. Sheila Jackson Lee's daughter, Erica Lee Carter, announced her candidacy Monday to finish the remainder of her mother's congressional term.

item.title: Court Gives Gun Rights Groups Big Win Vs. Biden's ATF
item.description: Gun rights advocates earned a significant victory Friday when the 8th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals determined the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives' (ATF) final rule on pistol stabilizing braces was "arbitrary and capricious."

item.title: Trump on X Taps Into a Voting Bloc That Legacy Media Doesn't Even Know Exists
Rural residents reveal how they feel about Gov Walz's 'very liberal' policies: 'We're mini California'
item.description: Rural Minnesotans spoke with Fox News Digital at "Farmfest" about their opinions on Democrat vice presidential nominee Gov. Tim Walz.

item.title: Huckabee to Newsmax: Biden Admits Truth of Dem Coup
item.description: Former Arkansas Gov. Mike Huckabee told Newsmax on Monday that President Joe Biden admitted there was a coup to take him out.

item.title: 'You'd Be Talking to Me From Another Realm': Musk to Trump on Near Miss of Assassination Attempt
'Squad' faces final primary challenge as 4 states go to polls Tuesday
item.description: Squad member Rep. Ilhan Omar faces a Democrat challenge as four states — Minnesota, Wisconsin, Connecticut and Vermont — hold primary elections on Tuesday.

item.title: Trump Decries 'Nonproductive' Illegal Migrants
item.description: Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump modified his line of attack on illegal immigration Monday, telling Elon Musk that in addition to dangerous people, countries are also sending the United States "nonproductive" illegal migrants.

item.title: Washington Post Reporter Wants Biden to Stop Trump-Musk Interview Because He Fears 'Misinformation'
Harris camp ducks questions on why Walz retired from military before completing coursework for high rank
item.description: The Harris campaign dodged Fox Digital's press inquiry asking why Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz did not complete U.S. Army Sergeants Major Academy coursework before retiring.

item.title: Trump Campaign: EU Tried to 'Meddle' in US Election
item.description: Donald Trump's campaign on Monday accused the European Union of trying to "meddle in the U.S. Presidential election," after an EU official posted an open letter to Elon Musk ahead of the X owner's sit-down with the former president, the New York Post reported.

item.title: Trump Campaign Office in Virginia Burglarized - Suspect Photos Released
Kamala Harris' campaign criticizes Trump for serving 'self-obsessed rich guys' after interview with Elon Musk
item.description: Kamala Harris' campaign slammed Trump's interview with Elon Musk, saying Trump's campaign is in the service of "self-obsessed rich guys who will sell out the middle class."

item.title: Docs Fear of Treating Ectopic Pregnancies Risks Women's Lives
item.description: Emergency room doctors are grappling with mortal, legal, and ethical dilemmas in treating ectopic pregnancies, a life-threatening condition where a fertilized egg implants outside the uterus.
